CatDescriptText: Dr. Charles R. Freebold, principal of A. Leo Weil School was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 9, 1960, pg. A1 with question: "Whom do you think the Democratic and the Republican parties will choose for their respective presidential candidates? Why?" Answer reads: "I think that the Democrats will nominate Adlai Stevenson, because he is the best qualified and also the least controversial of the candidates. There's no question that the Republicans will nominate Nixon because of his qualification, training, and his experience."
